						<p><hi rend="bold">King: ⎯⎯ Year: <hi rend="italic">Subhakṛit, Āṉi</hi> 12.</hi></p>						

						<p>This record is in characters of the 16th century A.D. It states that during the rule of Āṉandarājar Saheb, the <hi rend="italic">ūravar</hi> of Uvarichchēri and Tirumalait-dēvar agreed to grant a grove of 3/4 <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> of land for conducting sacred bath to the god Koḻundīśurasvāmiyār at Kōṭṭūr.</p>						

